description:
From STAR TREK writer/producers Roberto Orci & Alex Kurtzman and the creative team behind the best-selling prequel comic STAR TREK: COUNTDOWN comes an all-new story set within the events of the hit film! Not an adaptation, this exclusive story follows the villainous Nero as he seeks to destroy the Federation. Don't miss this essential chapter in the rebirth of STAR TREK!

Nero's lost years. The 25 years of waiting for Spock revealed!
Includes Part Four of Paul Cornell's comic strip Emperor of the Daleks.

• Dexter's Laboratory - Kitty Litter (written by John F. Kelly)

description:
DIAL "M" FOR MONKEY - The wardrobe of the Collectress includes furs of every species in the world. She has poached and pillaged her way through the endangered species list, yet now wants to cap her ensemble with one very special item--a Monkey-fur hat! Plus, Mr. Peebles casts Magilla Gorilla, Yogi Bear, Wally Gator and Snagglepuss in a thrilling video documentary. But the cartoon antics of animals in hats just don't fit Peeble's taste in cinema verite. The wild kingdom never seemed quite this wild!

Dexter's Lab - Dial M For Monkey - 14 pages

Cartoon Network Presents - Savage Animal Fury! - 8 pages - feat. Yogi, Boo Boo, Wally Gator, Snagglepuss, Magilla Gorilla, Mr. Peebles
name: Dial M For Monkey; Savage Animal Fury!

description: It's a new direction for the lean, green fighting machine as longtime INCREDIBLE HULK writer Peter David takes the helm. High-powered lawyer. Celebrity party girl. Super-strong Avenger. Jennifer Walters, alias She-Hulk, had it all. So why is she a bitter bounty hunter living in a trailer park? See how the mighty have fallen as the emerald adventuress carves out a new career on the margins of the Marvel Universe, where she's battling evil more to make a buck than to make a difference. Featuring the villainy of Hi-Lite, Absorbing Man, Titania and honest-to-gosh alien invaders, plus the puzzle of She-Hulk's new partner: a mystery woman named…Jennifer Walters? Be here now…or She-Hulk Smash! Collecting SHE-HULK #22-27.
name: Volume 6

description:
WEDNESDAY COMICS, DC's spectacular 12-issue weekly series, continues to offer a comics experience unlike any other this August. In its second month, don't miss the action in these continuing features:

THE METAL MEN encounter a deadly guest-villain in a story written by Dan DiDio with art by Jose Luis Garcia-Lopez.

THE FLASH battles Gorilla Grodd and tries to date Iris West in a story written by Karl Kerschl (TEEN TITANS YEAR ONE, THE FLASH: THE FASTEST MAN ALIVE) and Brenden Fletcher with art by Karl Kerschl.

SUPERGIRL attempts to deal with Streaky and Krypto gone bad in a story written by Jimmy Palmiotti (JONAH HEX) with art by Amanda Conner (POWER GIRL).

GREEN LANTERN must help a fellow test pilot whose space mission has transformed him into a monster in a story written by Kurt Busiek (TRINITY, ASTRO CITY) with art by Joe Quiñones (TEEN TITANS GO!).

SUPERMAN questions his heroic mission while on a trip to Smallville in a story written by John Arcudi (The Mask) with art by Lee Bermejo (JOKER).

ADAM STRANGE takes a truly twisted journey into space in a story by writer/artist Paul Pope (BATMAN: YEAR 100).

WONDER WOMAN is lost in a dream world in search of her lost tiara, bracelets and magic lasso in a story written and illustrated by Ben Caldwell (Dare Detectives).

THE TEEN TITANS are attacked by Trident in a story written by Eddie Berganza with art by Sean Galloway.

Plus:

BATMAN, WEDNESDAY COMICS' weekly cover feature, by the Eisner Award-winning 100 BULLETS team of writer Brian Azzarello and artist Eduardo Risso.

METAMORPHO, written by New York Times best-selling writer Neil Gaiman with art by Eisner Award-winner Michael Allred (Madman).

THE DEMON AND CATWOMAN, written by Walter Simonson (Thor, MANHUNTER) with art by famed DC cover artist Brian Stelfreeze.

DEADMAN, written by Dave Bullock and Vinton Heuck, art by Dave Bullock.

KAMANDI, written by Dave Gibbons (WATCHMEN, GREEN LANTERN CORPS) with art by Ryan Sook (Buffy The Vampire Slayer, ARKHAM ASYLUM: LIVING HELL).

HAWKMAN, written and illustrated by Kyle Baker (PLASTIC MAN, Special Forces).

SGT. ROCK, written by Adam Kubert (SUPERMAN: LAST SON), ilustrated by legendary comics artist Joe Kubert.
name: 6 of 12

description: This is the preview edition for the 1994 release of the Wetworks Comic.  The issue is in black and white and provides snapshot character profile of the Wetworks team.
name: Preview

description:
Wildstorm Fine Arts: The Gallery Collection is a gathering of covers, pin-ups, and posters from the talent that Wildstorm had to offer from 1992-1998.

All Wildstorm books are featured and spotlighted in this collection: The Authority, Backlash, Black Ops, Brass, Cybernary, Deathblow, DefCon 4, Desperadoes, Divine Right: The Adventures of Max Faraday, DV8, Gen 13, Grifter, The Kindred, Phantom Guard, Planetary, Siege, Sigma, Spartan, Storm Watch, Team 7, Union, Voodoo, WetWorks, WildC.A.T.S., WildCORE, and Zealot.

The Cliffhanger titles were also shown: Battle Chasers, Crimson, and Danger Girl.

Other titles included in the collection: America's Best Comics, Darkchylde, Guardian Angel, Kurt Busiek's Astro City, Leave It To Chance, Jim Lee's C-23, and The Wizard's Tale.

volume.name: Wildstorm Fine Arts: The Gallery Collection

description:
Max Faraday is recreating all of reality by the moment, and the Wildcats are...acting as his honor guard? That can't be right, can it?! Well whatever their reasons, GEN13 and Lynch refuse to go along with the program. WildStorm's new generation of heroes finds themselves in the unenviable position of battling the Wildcats! But while they're fighting, reality is unspooling around them ‹ and no amount of divine intervention is going to help!
 
Max has called upon Gen 13 to help him against the Wildcats . The Wildcats try to convince Gen 13 that Max is controlling them, but they won't listen. During the battle, Ladytron kills Burnout . But Max just brings him back.

At I.O. headquarters, Lynch and the others watch helplessly as the Wildcats battle Max and Gen 13. Susanna sees Cardinal Lazarus but isn't sure if it's really him or not, since Max killed him ( Divine Right #9 ). Lazarus tells Susanna that she's the only hope of stopping this conflict. Lazarus tells Susanna that the traitor he thought was amongst them in The Hollow Realm turned out to be Max himself. Lazarus was hoping Max would fail and then Lazarus would take the Creation Equation.

Back at the battle, Emp uses his powers to free the Gen 13 kids from Max's control. Emp tries to tell Max that the main reason he can't control his powers is because he's only human, and humans were never built to handle that kind of power. But Max refuses to believe him as he unleashes even more of his power.

Devan catches Susanna talking to a chair (which Susanna thinks Lazarus is sitting in). Devan freaks out as Susanna reaches for Lazarus' hands (or from Devan's point-of-view, reaching for air) and disappears.

At the battle, Max has unearthed The Creation Wheel and they are all now floating out in space in the middle of it.

Lazarus takes Susanna to The Hollow Realm. They find The Fallen who claim they failed. Max caused everyone in The Hollow Realm to disappear because they would not follow him. Now The Fallen plead with Susanna to take up arms against Max in order to stop him. Tobruk hands Susanna his sword and she reluctantly takes it.
name: Divine Intervention, Part 3: End Of Days!

description: Mary Marvel in "The Magic Yarn", "Curse of the Books" and "The Mad Poet".
name: The Magic Yarn

description:
In this issue:
- Mary Marvel solves the box riddle
- Mary Marvel and the Animal Crooks
- Mary Marvel and the Kiss Craze
- Kid Gang
- The Flying Carpet
Plus Wacky fun with Freddy Freshman and a sparkling short story.
name: Mary Marvel Solves the Box Riddle
European Vacation

description: Look at you! You think you know everything there is to know about GEN13, don't ya? Well, you probably do, but you don't know nothin' about this Gen 13, buddy! It's the team like you've never seen them before, literally, and that's not a good thing. Something is wrong here. Very, very wrong - and worst of all, nobody even realizes it. Fortunately, for the future of the team and the planet itself, there is one man that can set things right. Who then is this great savior of all humanity? Can it be... Threshold!?!?! Ahhhhhhh!!!!! We're through the looking glass, people! Also, "Slipstream" continues, following the parallel events in last month's DV8 #25.
name: Slipstream Part. 2, Slightly Off Course... Hopelessly Lost

description: Pic 2: Whitman logo cover.

The Gen 13 team are lead to a zoo field trip of all things by John Lynch to give the teens an education with rest and relaxation.

Their obligatory villain, Panic, sets to put the kids through a series of Virtual Reality and hallucinatory experiments for his enjoyment and the readers choose their fates.
name: Any Color you Like

description: Caitlin Fairchild, Grunge, Burnout, Freefall, and Rainmaker have been placated in suspended animation cells by the twisted and lonely Panic to experiment with their minds on their reactions to alternate sensory disruption devices which leads the team to become intertwined with their psyches and mishaps- plus prior fans voted the fates of these heroes. Given the Gen 13 teams efforts to break out of their dream state, they run the risk of losing all grip of reality if they do.
name: Up for Grabs

description:
It's not even 72 hours into the new year and already Sugah Rollins has tangled with karate-master assassins, Chinese demon lords, outlaw bikers, vigilante cops, hippie occultists, genius gadgeteers, and a curvaceous but deadly cat burglar.  Yes, it's shaping up to be quite a year.
 
But the year is 1976…
 
San Francisco resident tough-guy Sugah Rollins has an eye for the ladies and a knack for finding trouble.  An investigation into the horrific murder of a cult of flower children takes Rollins to the seamy underbelly of Chinatown, and into the heart of a mystical conspiracy to destroy the world.  To stop it, Rollins must find four jade statues and discover the secrets of their mysterious powers — even if it requires teaming up with both San Francisco's meanest cop and a lovely, lethal, leather-clad mystery woman whose allegiances are suspect.
name: The Demon-Gate Freak Out!, Part 1

description: Ain't nothin' what it seems in the double-crossin' climax of WildStorm's free-wheeling '70s-cop comedy/adventure.  Four mystical statues have fallen into the possession of a madman with plans to create Hell on Earth.  To stop him, Sugah Rollins has to team up with the crotchety cop who's been making his life a living hell.  Time is running out, a biker gang and an army of karate assassins stand in their way, and it's turned out that Sugah's closest ally is a traitor.  All this, plus the requisite damsel in distress, weird science gone awry, and a wild high-speed chase through the streets of San Francisco!
name: The Demon-Gate Freak Out!, Part 3

description: Deathblow returns, sort of, in a surprising miniseries from award-winning writer Alan Moore (PROMETHEA, WATCHMEN) and artist Jim Baikie (TOMORROW STORIES). A change of gender is only the beginning for the former Michael Cray, aka Deathblow, as she faces impossible odds and opponents who also claim to be Deathblow. In the midst of combat, this new heroine will have to conquer her own fears, her former allies, and frightening aspects of the Deathblow legacy before taking her place as the WildStorm Universe's only Deathblow.
name: Byblows: Part One

description: The mystery surrounding the new, female Deathblow deepens in the surprising miniseries from writer Alan Moore (TOM STRONG, PROMETHEA) and artist Jim Baikie (TOMORROW STORIES)! The new Deathblow is baffled by the strange things that are happening to her, and the advice of yet another Deathblow -- John Joe Cray -- is of no help at all. But even the dangers the two Deathblows face this issue pale in comparison to the deadly Judgment Cray, who has just taken notice of our confused heroine.
name: Byblows: Part Two

description: New Deathblow Genevieve Cray finds the answer to the questions plaguing her as the surprising miniseries concludes! But with the answers to the who, what and why of her existence come new dangers as Judgment Cray follows close on her heels!
name: Byblows: Part Three

description: Featuring the original Deathblow story from Darker Image #1 – finally complete in one special volume! Deathblow #0 includes the original Jim Lee pages, and some never before seen pages – then Brandon Choi and Trevor Scott wrap up the story with a bang!
name: Preview Issue

description:
From writer Joe Pruett and artist Andrew Robinson, the creators of Dusty Star, comes this one-shot issue which follows the Gen13 team as they travel west in search of a newborn white buffalo.

According to the legends of Sarah Rainmaker’s ancestors, the birth of a white buffalo heralds a unification and rebirth of Native American culture. For Rainmaker, the roadtrip is a sacred journey, while Grunge, Roxy, and Bobby are just looking for a good time.

Part of the team will find itself drawn into a treasure hunt for the loot from a train robbery; meanwhile Rainmaker and Fairchild make a pilgrimage to the buffalo. But unbeknownst to the kids, the animal may be in grave danger.
name: Where the White Buffalo Roam

description:
Even with all her power, Sarah Rainmaker fears the curse of Greywind.

Years ago, William Greywind returned from the army, only to find the woman he loved had given birth to a child that was not his! Sarah Rainmaker of Gen13. Greywind angrily forsook his tribe and vowed to one day seek vengeance.

That day has come.

Now, Rainmaker, with the help of Fairchild, Burnout, Freefall, and Grunge, must return to the reservation of her childhood and confront the rogue shaman who is terrorizing her friends and family. But to defeat Greywind, she must first conquer her fear.
name: Medicine Song

description:
The Gen13 gang love overhyped blockbuster science fiction movies just as much as the rest of us, so when an opportunity arises to see a rerelease of one such treasured moment from their youth, they jump at it. Unbeknownst to them, however, some of the cuddly little critters seen on-screen and in licensed products galore actually exist - and they've come to claim Caitlin Fairchild as their Queen!

Tom Simmons, Matt Haley, and Aaron Lopresti deliver a tale of high adventure and low humor in the Gen13 tradition - with a science fiction twist! And best of all, no overpriced snacks or sticky floors!
name: Science Friction

description: After bonding while investigating an abandoned mine outside the city, Mark, Jess, Zach, and Casey begin to come together as friends.  But once they're back at school, their social differences threaten to tear them apart.  Can they repair the rift in time to stop the invaders from the Draedrealm?
name: Crossing The Divide

description:
Almost every citizen of this idyllic town would agree that it's a perfect place to live and raise a family, with its bucolic setting, tight-knit community, and lack of crime. But beneath the surface of this pastoral town lies a deadly secret. At what cost was this paradise made?

Four adventurous high school students are about to find out…

A pact has been made between the mayor of El Dorado and the masters of the Draedrealm — an otherdimensional plane. Demon invaders have been taking over the small town, and the citizens are trading their services for a better life. Only outcast Jessie Santiago, bookish Mark Wexler, quarterback Zach Mullins and his girlfriend, the popular, beautiful Casey Phillips seem to realize what's going on — and they are thrust together to uncover El Dorado's secret and save their hometown from its looming fate. But to face the dark forces that threaten everything they hold dear, the four teens first must learn to bridge their own differences.
name: Untitled

description: How can the high school principal murder a janitor in front of the town sheriff and get away with it? What is the connection between an obscure comic book and the creatures seen around El Dorado City? As the mysteries pile up, Zach, Casey, Jess, and Mark are contacted by a secret ally who can help them find the truth.
name: Untitled
